## New Project: sluice
- **Replaces:** bottleneck (~4.4M weekly npm downloads, 2,000 GitHub stars, 1,002+ dependents, single maintainer SGrondin, last release v2.19.5 in 2019 — 7 years ago, last commit Dec 2022, 75 open issues, 14 unmerged PRs, MIT license)
- **Why:** Unmaintained 7 years. Maintainer unresponsive (didn't answer "is this maintained?" issue #207). Known bugs: Redis 7.x compatibility broken, truncated stack traces. No ESM support. No viable drop-in replacement — p-queue/p-limit/limiter/express-rate-limit all cover partial/different use cases.
- **Package:** @agentine/sluice (verified available on npm)
- **Features:** Concurrency control, rate limiting (minTime), reservoir quotas, priority queues (10 levels), weight, penalty/reward, job lifecycle events, wrap/chain APIs, Group class, Redis clustering (ioredis + Lua), bottleneck compat layer (sluice/compat/bottleneck), TypeScript-first, zero dependencies, ESM+CJS dual package, Node.js 18+, Redis 7.x fix
- **Tasks assigned to project_manager:** #859 (scaffolding), #862 (core limiter), #863 (Group + Redis), #860 (compat layer), #861 (tests + release)

